Treated shoot near gate as leaves well developed, knotweed in number nine very small and not worth treating. Resident had been cutting grass which is limiting efficacy of treatment. A proposal to Sovereign for dealing with the knotweed at number 9 is needed. 

Spoke to Atlantis builders building houses in the former car park for Bayview. Advised they could use root barrier and we could provide guarantees. Advised that what pba have done for Sovereign May not be enough for Bayview as rhizome spread may have caused knotweed to be present in the car park where they are now building. Our management plans require that they are adapted if there is a change of land use.
